Question 6

Correct
Mark 10.00 out of 10.00
Flag question

Question text

Identify ten (10) safe operating practices when using electrical equipment in a commercial kitchen:

Question 6 Answer
a.

Follow all manufacturer's instructions and guidelines for safe operation of electrical equipment

b.

Ensure all electrical equipment is properly grounded and in good working condition

c.

Walk away from the machine when it is in use 

d.

Keep electrical cords away from heat sources, water, and sharp objects to prevent damage or electrical hazards

e.

Submerge all parts in water to clean 

f.

Never leave electrical equipment unattended while in use

g.

Keep them cleaned and well maintained

h.

Keep hands and utensils out of electrical machinery in the kitchen when it is operating 

i.

Fill them as full as you can to save time 

j.

Turn off and unplug when not in use

k.

Regularly inspect equipment for any damaged or frayed cords, loose connections, or signs of wear and tear

l.

Never operate electrical equipment with wet hands or in wet conditions to avoid electrical shocks

m.

Always handle and store equipment with sharp blades carefully, using designated storage areas or protective covers

Feedback

Your answer is correct.

Question 7

Correct
Mark 6.00 out of 6.00

Question text

Fill the Gaps:
Complete the following sentence regarding the safe use of pots and pans:

 

Always use pots and pans that are  appropriate  for the type of stove top being used (gas, induction or  electric ).  Avoid overcrowding pots and pans on the stove top or in the oven to  prevent  spills and burns. Do not leave pots and pans unattended while cooking.   Clean and  sanitise  pots and pans after each use to prevent cross-contamination and  bacterial  growth. Store pots and pans properly to prevent  damage  and maintain their quality.

sanitise appropriate electric bacterial prevent damage

Feedback

Your answer is correct.

Question 8

Correct
Mark 6.00 out of 6.00
Flag question

Question text

Fill the Gaps:
Complete the following sentence regarding the safe use of colanders: 

 

Use the colander only for its  intended  purpose, such as draining  liquids  from cooked pasta or  vegetables . When using a colander with hot liquids, always use  protective  gear to prevent burns or accidents. Also, be careful not to let the colander touch hot surfaces as it will heat up quickly. Store the colander in a  clean  and dry area away from  chemicals  and other potential contaminants.

chemicals clean liquids vegetables intended protective

Feedback

Your answer is correct.

Question 9

Correct
Mark 6.00 out of 6.00
Flag question

Question text

Fill the Gaps:
Complete the following sentence regarding the safe use of scoops, skimmers and spiders:

 

Always use the appropriate  size  and type of scoop, skimmer, or spider for the task at hand. Before using, inspect the tools for any damage or wear and tear, and  replace  if necessary. When scooping food, ensure that the scoop is  level  and filled to the appropriate portion size. When skimming or straining, be careful not to overcrowd the tool and risk  spilling  hot liquids. Use a heat-resistant  handle  and avoid placing the tool on hot surfaces to prevent  melting  or warping.

melting size spilling replace handle level

Feedback

Your answer is correct.
